      "author": "aniruddh-jammoria",
      "description": "AgentBoard 2.0 makes the board the visual half of an agent-driven workflow: an AI agent scores your tasks into a Markdown file, and the board renders, ranks, and lets you edit them — writing every change back to the file.\r\n\r\n**What's new**\r\n- 🎯 Priority scores per task (urgency, importance, effort) as a color-coded `U | I | E` pill\r\n- ✏️ Edit scores, due dates, and critical flag right on the board — with a built-in calendar picker\r\n- 📅 Due dates with overdue highlighting\r\n- 🤝 Your edits are flagged so the agent won't overwrite them\r\n- 🎨 Calmer critical styling + a \"last updated\" timestamp\r\n\r\nTask format: `- [ ] Book dentist appointment [U:2 I:2 T:4 E:S Due:18-Jul-2026 Crit:Y]` — see the [README](https://github.com/aniruddh-jammoria/obsidian-agentic-todolist#todo-file-format) for details.\r\n\r\n**Install:** download `main.js`, `manifest.json`, and `styles.css` below into `<vault>/.obsidian/plugins/agent-board/`.",
